From 2352d837aa1c7a53fa546bb4918afe3129fb42dc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ben Cressey <bcressey@amazon.com>
Date: Wed, 21 May 2025 21:00:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] build: do not build examples

The examples expect the libraries they link with to have been built
with an embedded rpath, in order to resolve the dependencies of those
libraries. This leads to linker warnings like the following:

  warning: liburcu-common.so.8, needed by liburcu-cds.so, not found
  (try using -rpath or -rpath-link)

We don't need the examples, so just stop building them.

Signed-off-by: Ben Cressey <bcressey@amazon.com>
---
 Makefile.am | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile.am b/Makefile.am
index 539a2ca..bea30de 100644
--- a/Makefile.am
+++ b/Makefile.am
@@ -4,7 +4,7 @@
 
 ACLOCAL_AMFLAGS=-I m4
 
-SUBDIRS = include src doc tests extras
+SUBDIRS = include src tests extras
 
 dist_doc_DATA = \
 	LICENSE.md \
-- 
2.49.0

